@faithwhite4345 People wanted animation to feel more mature for once, but they got offended by the juvenile humor, specifically when it comes to Illumination Studios. 

(Out of topic statement) For me, the films of Illumination Studios are average yet soulless cash grabs everyone has been talking about. In my opinion, the story and the concepts need some improvement and the CGI animation is top notch in quality, but wasted over a plotline. However, I do understand about the hatred towards Illumination simply because of the "it's for kids" stigma which it explains about the bland, dumber comedies which it makes you feel like you are out of touch with reality. Maybe Illumination Studios should left those childish things behind and step up the game into something more challenging, even if I just called it a day. 

Raya and the Last Dragon will probably become successful despite being flawed but the "con-baby" argument is pretty ridiculous considering the fact that Disney also has a history of wacky and comedic undertones while keeping up straight. The dragon character design is maybe justified but it doesn't matter.

@Aethelhadas It's supposed to draw inspiration from all over South East Asia, not just a specific country but the region as a whole. 

The design of Raya's sword and clothing is based on traditional garb and weapons seen all throughout the region. As I said before, Sisu is designed from the mythical water serpents common in many SEA mythology.

Particularly, the temples remind me of Thai architecture. The martial arts are reminiscent of the Filipino Kali, with her Eskrima sticks specifically, as is seen in the first teaser trailer.

